<example name="start and end points">
  <text>
    The government's borrowing authority dropped to $2.8 trillion from
    $2.87 trillion.  
  </text>
  <arg n="1">the government's borrowing authority</arg>
  <rel>dropped</rel>
  <arg f="to" n="4">$2.8 trillion</arg>
  <arg f="from" n="3">$2.87 trillion</arg>
</example>

<example name="extent">
  <text>
    The stock market dropped nearly 7% Oct 13.
  </text>
  <arg n="1">The stock market</arg>
  <rel>dropped</rel>
  <arg f="EXT" n="2">nearly 7%</arg>
  <arg f="TMP" n="M">Oct 13</arg>
</example>

<note>
  Let's use EXT for numericals only, otherwise Arg2-MNR:
</note>

<example name="manner">
